name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
tweet: These listening sessions are crucial, and tomorrow we plan to do the same in Northern Nevada.   I’m here as a Lieutenant Governor, but more importantly as an educator and parent of three daughters. @NVSupt and I will never stop fighting for our students.  https://t.co/iYXEYEWueG

name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
tweet: Finally we listened to school leaders. It wasn’t that long ago I was a principal, and can relate to the struggles administrators are facing. You have an advocate in state government, and I appreciate everyone airing their concerns today.  https://t.co/DaLsrkclZC

name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
tweet: After that we talked with teachers, the ones who see first-hand what is happening in schools. It’s not just students who are struggling — our teachers are overworked and overstressed. We cannot forget about what teachers do for us all day, every day.  https://t.co/nYRnkTrHbr

name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
tweet: Next we heard from parents and community leaders. We in this room are the ones who need to take charge and move our schools forward — together.  https://t.co/xIDs8gBvNX

name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
tweet: Our first roundtable was with local education agency leaders. We as the adults need to be the ones to build a community where students can learn safely. It was important to hear from so many different and diverse voices to find ways to do that.  https://t.co/xfTjVMGWYo

name: Lt. Governor Lisa Cano Burkhead
